Preventing XSS (C#)
Question:
Fill in the blank to encode user input in C# to prevent Cross-Site Scripting (XSS) vulnerabilities when displaying user input on a webpage.

csharp

@__________(userInput)  // Fill in the blank
Expected Answer:
The blank should be filled with Html.Encode.

Explanation:
The @Html.Encode(userInput) method ensures that any special characters in the user input are encoded to HTML entities. This prevents any injected JavaScript or HTML from being executed, protecting against XSS attacks.

